<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1573] Unsafe synchronization in NetworkServerControlImpl</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1573</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;NetworkServerControlImpl has some constructs like this one:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    if (logWriter != null)&lt;br/&gt;
    {&lt;br/&gt;
        synchronized(logWriter) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            logWriter.println(msg);
        }
&lt;p&gt;    }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since logWriter might be set to null after the test for logWriter!=null and before synchronized(logWriter), one might get a NullPointerException. It would be safer to write this instead:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    PrintWriter lw = logWriter;&lt;br/&gt;
    if (lw != null) {&lt;br/&gt;
        synchronized (lw) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            lw.println(msg);
        }
&lt;p&gt;    }&lt;/p&gt;</description>
